    "---\n",
    "## 11. Information Ratio (IR)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theorie\n",
    "\n",
    "Die **Information Ratio** misst die **Fähigkeit eines aktiven Managers**, konsistent **Alpha gegenüber einer Benchmark** zu generieren:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$IR = \\frac{\\alpha}{\\sigma_{\\text{Active}}} = \\frac{\\overline{r_p - r_b}}{\\sigma(r_p - r_b)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- $\\alpha$: Durchschnittlicher **Active Return** (Portfolio minus Benchmark)\n",
    "- $\\sigma_{\\text{Active}}$: **Tracking Error** – Volatilität des Active Returns\n",
    "\n",
    "### Tracking Error\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tracking Error (TE)** = Standardabweichung der Renditedifferenz (Portfolio - Benchmark). Misst wie stark der Manager von der Benchmark abweicht:\n",
    "- Niedriger TE (< 1%): Quasi-Indexfonds\n",
    "- Mittlerer TE (2–5%): Typisches aktives Management\n",
    "- Hoher TE (> 8%): Sehr aktives Management oder konzentriertes Portfolio\n",
    "\n",
    "### Das Fundamental Law of Active Management (Grinold)\n",
    "\n",
    "$$IR \\approx IC \\cdot \\sqrt{BR}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- **IC (Information Coefficient):** Korrelation zwischen Prognosen und tatsächlichen Renditen (typisch 0.05–0.10)\n",
    "- **BR (Breadth):** Anzahl unabhängiger Investitionsentscheidungen pro Jahr\n",
    "\n",
    "Das bedeutet: Ein Manager mit bescheidener Skill (IC=0.05) aber 100 unabhängigen Trades pro Jahr erreicht IR ≈ 0.5 – besser als ein Manager mit IC=0.1 aber nur 10 Trades pro Jahr (IR ≈ 0.32). **Diversifikation der Entscheidungen ist genauso wichtig wie Skill.**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Quelle:** Grinold & Kahn (1999), Kap. 6 & 7"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Benchmark und aktiv verwaltetes Portfolio ─────────────────────────────────\n",
    "r_benchmark = pd.Series(np.random.normal(0.0003, 0.010, T))   # DAX-ähnlich\n",
    "\n",
    "# Aktiver Manager: leicht positives Alpha, aber Tracking Error\n",
    "active_return = pd.Series(np.random.normal(0.00012, 0.004, T))  # Active Returns\n",
    "r_portfolio   = r_benchmark + active_return\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Information Ratio berechnen ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "active_ret_ann  = active_return.mean() * TRADING_DAYS\n",
    "tracking_error  = active_return.std()  * np.sqrt(TRADING_DAYS)\n",
    "ir              = active_ret_ann / tracking_error\n",
    "\n",
    "# Kumulativer Vergleich\n",
    "cum_bench = (1 + r_benchmark).cumprod()\n",
    "cum_port  = (1 + r_portfolio).cumprod()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Active Return (ann.)  : {active_ret_ann*100:.3f}%')\n",
    "print(f'Tracking Error (ann.) : {tracking_error*100:.3f}%')\n",
    "print(f'Information Ratio     : {ir:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'\\nFundamental Law Check (IC=0.05, BR=100): IR ≈ {0.05*np.sqrt(100):.3f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].plot(cum_bench.values, color='#95a5a6', lw=2, label='Benchmark')\n",
    "axes[0].plot(cum_port.values,  color='#2ecc71', lw=2, label=f'Portfolio (IR={ir:.2f})')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Portfolio vs. Benchmark', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Kumulativer Wert')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rollender Information Ratio\n",
    "roll_ir = pd.Series([\n",
    "    (active_return.iloc[max(0,i-63):i].mean() * TRADING_DAYS) /\n",
    "    (active_return.iloc[max(0,i-63):i].std()  * np.sqrt(TRADING_DAYS))\n",
    "    if active_return.iloc[max(0,i-63):i].std() > 0 else 0\n",
    "    for i in range(63, T)\n",
    "])\n",
    "axes[1].plot(roll_ir.values, color='#3498db', lw=1.5)\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(ir,   color='green',  ls='--', lw=1.5, label=f'Gesamt IR={ir:.2f}')\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(0,    color='black',  lw=0.8)\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(0.5,  color='orange', ls=':', lw=1, label='IR=0.5 (gut)')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Rollender Information Ratio (63-Tage)', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Information Ratio')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('information_ratio.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
